{|{{Infobox ship begin}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image= |Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country= |Ship flag= {{USN flag|1942}} |Ship name=USS ''Bunting'' |Ship namesake= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder= |Ship laid down= |Ship launched=1935, as SS ''Vagabond'' |Ship acquired=22 October 1940 |Ship commissioned=6 June 1941 |Ship in service= |Ship out of service= |Ship renamed=''Bunting'', 6 November 1940 |Ship reclassified= |Ship refit= |Ship struck=24 June 1942 |Ship reinstated= |Ship homeport= |Ship motto= |Ship nickname= |Ship honors= |Ship fate=Sunk after collision, 3 June 1942 |Ship status= |Ship notes= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship type= [[Coastal minesweeper]] |Ship displacement= {{convert|115|LT|t|0|abbr=on}} |Ship length= {{convert|79|ft|3|in|m|abbr=on}} |Ship beam= {{convert|21|ft|6|in|m|abbr=on}} |Ship draft= {{convert|9|ft|6|in|m|abbr=on}} |Ship depth= |Ship hold depth= |Ship propulsion= |Ship speed= {{convert|8.5|kn|lk=in}} |Ship complement=16 |Ship armament=2 Ã— .30 cal. [[machine gun]]s |Ship armor= |Ship notes= }} |} '''USS ''Bunting'' (AMc-7)''' was a coastal [[Minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]] in the [[United States Navy]]. She was named after the [[bunting (bird)|bunting]], a seed eating bird intermediate in size between [[starling]]s and [[finch]]es.
== Acquisition and modification == SS ''Vagabond'', a wooden-hulled [[purse seiner]] built in 1935 at [[Tacoma, Washington]], by the Martinac Shipbuilding Co. was acquired by the Navy from Marko Bokich, et al., on 22 October 1940. She was designated '''AMc-7''' shortly thereafter; renamed USS ''Bunting'' on 6 November 1940; converted to a coastal minesweeper by the Campbell Machine Company at [[San Diego, California]]. She was placed in service at the Destroyer Base, San Diego, on 6 June 1941, Ens. Paul H. McBride, [[USNR]], in command.
== Assigned to San Francisco Bay duties == Assigned to the 12th Naval District, ''Bunting'' reported to her assigned base at the Section Headquarters, [[Treasure Island (California)|Treasure Island]], [[San Francisco, California]], on 19 June and spent the remainder of the year 1941 and the first five months of 1942 engaged in training officers, minesweeping, patrolling [[San Francisco Bay]], and participating in local Army and Navy exercises.
== Collision and sinking == While patrolling from [[Line Mile Rock]] to [[Point Diablo]], ''Bunting'' collided with the patrol craft {{USS|PC-569||2}} on 3 June 1942 and sank. Her name was struck from the [[Naval Vessel Register|Navy List]] on 24 June 1942.
